{
  "texts": [
    "Hungarian has a gender-neutral pronoun ö which can be translated into English as either he, she or gender-neutral they.",
    "These translations were generated by Google Translate.",
    "1 are wrong from a linguistic point of view, they do exhibit a fair amount of bias and stereotyping when it comes to opting for the feminine or masculine pronoun in the automatically generated English translations.",
    "In a systematic examination of this gender bias phenomenon, Prates et al. (2020) translated sentences containing professions from 12 different gender-neutral language (including Hungarian) into English and examined how often female, male or gender-neutral pronouns appeared in the translations.",
    "Their analysis not only revealed a significant imbalance in the distribution of pronouns but also highlighted that this imbalance exceeds the gender disparities observed in society itself for fields such as STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics)."
  ]
}